	   <a name=98752195668270></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98752195668270><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>My way to lvl 50</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 17th 11:39 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok this post will be a bit long, but it will explai alot of things for you, I currently have a lvl 53 chanter, and working up a new one, so here is some tips.<br><br>Now I will post this the minor twinked way, that means you dont have to concentrate on items, I assume you got some, and I assume you got money.<br><br>lvl 1 to 4<br>I hunt them in the newbie areas, and I try to kill as many fire beetles as I can. Dont waste money on the lvl 1 spells, since they arent any good.<br><br>lvl 4 to 8<br>First hing to do is train 1 point in meditate, and get your mez and pet spell. Summon a pet, and keep casting mez on it, and work up the conjuration skill, since your future life depends on it, max it out every level till 30 (hell levels tends to max out spell skills, and 45 will do for sure). These levels start heading towards zones like EC, North Ro, BB (butcher block), QH. I will not advise people to hunt in dungeons, since your mez is short duration, and low level dungeons tends to be trainstations.<br><br>lvl 8 to 12<br>These levels are hard, I used my time there hunting low blue cons, since our level 8 spells sucks. work you way through these levels and you will soon be wanted.<br><br>lvl 12 to 16<br>If your smart, and you can get a druid along, charm can be very good. Druid snares a monster, and you charm it and send it on another monster, and you can end up making these levels in very short time. Also be sure to get memblur and keep it memmed all the time. Also Kerra Isle near Tox forest is extremely good xp, it now got a 20% xp bonus, and there are plenty of cats to kill there, beware of caster mobs tho.<br><br>lvl 16 to 20<br>Get breeze, first spell of them all to get, and be sure to train research. After that, head to Lake R. Find another one to group with and go for aviak guards. Be sure to have your lvl 16 pet first tho. You should spens all your time here to lvl 20.<br><br>lvl 20 to 24<br>You get specialization here, and many chooses alteration, but I am more into crowd control now, and have done the quest in the temple and change from alteration to conjuration, its a delicate choise we have to make here, so think it through.<br>Now where do we hunt here ? well, we are starting to show ourself now, and we are started to get wanted, but I would recomend places like Lake of Ill Omen and South Karana. Many chanters tends to stay in the lake and solo there, but I hate to stay on a single target spawn, since I have a habbit of falling asleep then :)<br><br>lvl 24 to 29<br>This is what I call nightmare for spells, since 29 is not far away, and there we get all the sweeeet spells, but if you can get into a group at the gnoll spires outside Infected Paw in South Karana, the way to 29 is fast.<br><br>lvl 29 to 34<br>Time to go constant /rol when you don't have group, since clarity beggers will make your life horrible (hear that droods ?). Now at this level I would surely go to either Crystal Caverns or Cazic Thule. Both places are good xp, and CC has sweet loot as well. Just enter the zone, make a /ooc Chanter seeks group, and you should have one.<br><br>lvl 34 to 39<br>Many people would say lower guk, but I wouldent recomend it. Overthere, good xp, and teamed up with one of those horrible droods you can make xp really fast, and the lvl 35 will be a piece of cake.<br><br>lvl 39 to 44<br>New charm spell here, and life begins to get really sweet. Now I dident really use the charm all that much, its to dangerous, but very fun. I spend my time in Dreadlands in one of the typical north wall groups, and let it take the time I needed. I also spend whole lvl 40 in lower guk, but more to learn different tactics how to play the class, and then back to dreadlands at 41 to make the sweet xp.<br><br>lvl 44 to 49<br>Now is the time to use our true power, crowd control. But where ? Burning Woods giant fort. But giants can't be mezzed all chanters might say ? Guess again, these giants are the only giants in the entire game that can be mezzed and stunned, so head there and work up some really phat xp, and when the puller pulls more than one giant, just mez one of them, and keep it mezzed and your group will love it. I made 45 here in 12 hours with a full group, and many of them was lvl 50 and 51, but the xp was sweet. With my speed buffing and clarity, the entire group was rolling, and we had 12 hours of constant pullings.<br><br>lvl 49+<br>Get your sebilis key, all I have to say, and be sure to buy Theft of Thought ASAP.<br><br>Different tactics.<br>AO Groups : AE groups are extremely good xp, but also very dangerous. A group is normally like this, 1 puller, 3 wizards, 1 cleric, 1 enchanter. Puller pulls 3 to 20 mobs (10 mobs+ is very hard, but it can be done, but make sure they all die on first blast form the wizards), and your job as enchanter is to keep all these mezzed, and the best way is to use aoe mez (the lvl 16 research spell, or the 51 trade in spell). You aoe mez wont last for very long, but will take alot of targets. I will not recommend these kinda groups to anyone below lvl 44, since this relay alot on the enchanter, and if things gets dicy your dead in 5 seconds. Over at www.graffe.com they have some tactics as well on this. and btw, record is 40 mobs or so in split paw with two groups using supernova. Also use /showspelleffects off here to reduce lag (you should at all time after 39 in full groups), and use /serverfilter on at all time and turn off others hits in chat filter.<br><br>Normal grouping.<br>Always make sure your tanks knows how to use /assist, otherwise teach them. /assist is gods gift to the enchanter if the tanks knows how to use it. Now to the buffings and debuffing. I tend to go far shamans to group with, so they can stat buff the tanks, and slow the mobs, and backup healing is nice as well. The I use the low duration speedbuffs, like aclarity, swift, aq, and then I concentrate 100% on the crowd control, and only speed buff the tanks as we go along, also keep clarity/clarity2 on the casters. Also make sure people DONT use aoe spells of any kind, since it will break mezzes, also make sure the people using dots are using assist (necromancer, druids and shamans), since dotted mobs cant be mezzed, and you will soon find yourself in trouble.<br>Now if your grouped with 6 people key thing is NO DOWNTIME, if you got alot of downtime, its not worth it, no matter how high the group bonus should be now.<br>Now what kind of groups should you go for ? Hard to tell, depends on where you hunt, but I go for these groups. 1 cleric, 1 evacer, 1 shaman, 1 monk, 2 tanks (1 warrior at least). Now who should you pick as evaccer then, I would take the wizard, and get a ranger as 2nd tank, and the reason for this is simple, wizards can make ALOT of damage fast, and the rangers can snare and do alot of damage as well, and by that the druid is useless. Also I would tell the ranger to leave the taunting to the warrior, so the cleric can concentrate on healing the warrior alone.<br><br>So how does /assist work ? ok...here it is, main tank should always be the one you assist, and he should make a button like this "/group Assist me in killing %t", and all others should make one like this "/assist &lt;the tanks name&gt;", keep tapping it till you see the mob as your target, now your assisting him, and you should all be on the same target.<br><br>Now the final advise from me is this, use eq.castersrealm.com and read about your spells, and learn your spells well. Learn how to do crowd control, and exspect to die alot.<br><br>Fazzi Fizzler<br>27th Erudite Enchanter (agnostic)<br>Brell Serilis server<br><br>Thakasis Shadowbringer<br>RETIRED 53th Inky Enchanter of Innoruuk<br>Brell Serilis Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
